oai_dc:dc.dc:title: W.L. Clement at newly constructed stream channel
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: W.L. Clement, SCS, prepares to check out newly constructed stream channel which was a part of a farm conservation plan. Length of channel is seven hundred and fifty fett long, two feet deep, with a ten foot bottom; the side slopes at a two to one angle.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
